parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, especially when making left turns, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the power steering fails at low speeds
the vehicle pulls to the right
and the steering wheel feels like it has no power assist.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion can cause the steering system to malfunction, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle makes a clunking or grinding noise
and the steering system feels like it is binding or sticking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Other related issues, such as steering fluid leaks and faulty steering components, can also contribute to power steering failure and rack and pinion failure, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
Engine compartment fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire under the hood
and the vehicle may be totaled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause engine failure, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: oil spots on the garage floor
and the smell of oil inside the passenger compartment.
